<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Sunalta</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Sunalta is bordered by the Bow River in the North, the Shaganappi golf course on the East, 17 Avenue to the South and 14 Street on the East, making Sunalta one of the most accessible and best connected neighborhoods in Calgary.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Houses in Sunalta are more affordable than the more luxurious neighborhoods in Calgary. The average asking price for houses in Sunalta is $336,000. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Sunalta has a lot of investment opportunities for buyers, with its high-density housing and single-family homes. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Sunaltaâ€™s real estate is mostly comprised of apartments and condominiums, making up 85.8% of the property and 83% of the housing is being used for rental purposes. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">As of 2005, Sunalta has an area redevelopment plan.</p>
        </div>
